x4freetext: 14 UD Pelletron Accelerator
Overall uncertainty in beam energy is less than 30 keV.
Natural carbon foil of thickness 50 ug/cm2
(for 12C(16O,a0)24Mg) and 104 ug/cm2 (for others)
Three surface barrier detector telescopes were set at
6, 9 and 16 degrees to the beam direction.
The telescope set at 9 degree was of 11 mm diameter at
a distance of 13.3 cm from the target subtending a
solid angle of 5.37 msr with angular acceptance of
+/-2.36 degree at the target. The depletion layer
thickness of dE and E detectors were 30 um and 2 mm
respectively.
The telescope set at 6 and 9 degree were of depletion
layer thicknesses 40 um and 2 mm for dE and E
detectors respectively.
For angular distribution measurements for the reaction
12C(16O,a0)24Mg, six surface barrier detectors of
2 mm thickness were used which were set 10 degree
apart at distances of 17.9-20.5 cm from the target
subtending solid angles of 0.76-1.5 msr with an
angular acceptance of about +/- 0.7 degree.
One more surface barrier detector of 300 um thickness
was also mounted which was used as a monitor for the
angular distribution measurements to normalize the
data.
